Kubernetes Dashboard Through Traefik
text:
have a Kubernetes cluster (release 1.23.4) working using Traefik(release 2.7.0). I would like to access the kubernetes dashboard through IngressRoute Traefix, everything seems to work correctly no error in the log of the Traefik pod and the dashboard but when i want to access the kubernetes dashboard it can not access the page: https://k8sdash.kub.techlabnews.com/api/v1/login/status and I have an error 404.(log in the firefox console).

Use this code for create the IngressRoute :

apiVersion: traefik.containo.us/v1alpha1 kind: ServersTransport metadata: name: kubernetes-dashboard-transport namespace: kubernetes-dashboard

spec: serverName: "k8sdash.kub.techlabnews.com" insecureSkipVerify: true

--- apiVersion: traefik.containo.us/v1alpha1 kind: IngressRoute metadata: name: kubernetes-dashboard namespace: kubernetes-dashboard spec: entryPoints: - websecure routes: - kind: Rule match: Host(`k8sdash.kub.techlabnews.com`) services: - kind: Service port: 443 name: kubernetes-dashboard namespace: kubernetes-dashboard serversTransport: kubernetes-dashboard-transport tls: secretName: kub.techlabnews-com-cert-secret-replica

Ask HN: Which tools increased your productivity the most?
text:
For me it's been Gitpod (https://gitpod.io). It's like CI for development environments. It integrates with Git and lets me build my project continuously, and then create a containerized environment with the latest artifacts that I connect to with my IDE. I like it so much I decided to build a self-hosted alternative. It's at https://hocus.dev if you want to check it out.

What are yours?

Ask HN: Resources for Understanding the Data Industry
text:
I am looking for resources to better understand how the data industry works. Specifically I am referring to companies that sell/productize actual data, not data manipulation software (such as databases).

Some questions I would like to answer: What data is available, who sells it, who uses it, what is it used for, how much does it cost, what platforms are used to buy/sell data, etc.

I am a data science professional that would like to start my own business. I have experience on the technical side (with statistics and forecasting) but I don't know much about how the business side of things works outside my niche industry, or where to start when it comes to starting a company. I have no idea if any data product I develop would be potentially valuable to customers, and how I would market or distribute it.

Any resources, links or ideas would be much appreciated. I apologize if this question sounds to vague or unspecific, unfortunately google isn't very helpful in this regard.

Ask HN: Self-hosted business model vs. SaaS
text:
I've been impressed by Sidekiq not just as a product, but also by its creator, Mike Perham's execution. It's a downloadable Ruby gem file that users self-host, which minimizes the need for 24/7 DevOps and streamlines customer support since it's really a straightforward solution to a straightforward problem.

Each time I think about a business idea in some field that I really enjoy, I always end up thinking of a SaaS: platform or a tool for analysis, which would require a larger team if I want it to scale, instead of being a one-person operation.

Is there a way to break away from this SaaS-focused mindset I have and embrace the self-hosted model that some products out there have successfully implemented?
